		<title>How to Easily Memorise ALL the Notes on the Bass Fingerboard</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-tips/easily-memorise-notes-bass-fingerboard.html</link>
		<comments>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-tips/easily-memorise-notes-bass-fingerboard.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 18 Jan 2017 11:37:18 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[scott]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Bass Tips]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=16013</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>=== Figuring out where the notes on the fingerboard are is pretty easy... open google, search "notes on bass fingerboard", click "images" and there you'll have a gazzilion diagrams all showing you where the notes are... BUT - the real...</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-tips/easily-memorise-notes-bass-fingerboard.html">How to Easily Memorise ALL the Notes on the Bass Fingerboard</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/AuS5wwr7MjI" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
<p>===</p>
<p>Figuring out where the notes on the fingerboard are is pretty easy... open google, search "notes on bass fingerboard", click "images" and there you'll have a <a href="https://www.google.co.uk/search?q=notes+on+bass+fretboard&amp;biw=1433&amp;bih=771&amp;source=lnms&amp;tbm=isch&amp;sa=X&amp;sqi=2&amp;ved=0ahUKEwj-5MiWzcvRAhWBWxoKHR2nD5AQ_AUIBigB" target="_blank">gazzilion diagrams</a> all showing you where the notes are...</p>
<p>BUT - the real work comes when you start to try and memorise the <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/beginners/learn-notes-bass-guitar-l197.html">notes on the fingerboard</a>. That's the tricky bit!</p>
<p>In this lesson I'm going to show you a super easy to understand exercise that's going to help you memorise all the notes over the entire fingerboard in an easy to manage systematic way.</p>
<p>Ready? Let's do this!</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed...</p>
